AN ACT relating to periods of observance; [designating the month of September of
each year as “Perimenopause Awareness Month” in this State;]
designating the month of October of each year as “Menopause
Awareness Month” in this State; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, certain days, weeks and months of observance are recognized in this
2 State. (NRS 236.018-236.095) [Sections 2 and] Section 3 of this bill [, respectively, designate:
3 (1) the month of September of each year as “Perimenopause Awareness Month”; and (2)]
4 designates the month of October of each year as “Menopause Awareness Month” in the State
5 of Nevada [. Additionally, sections 2 and 3 require] and requires the Governor to issue
6 annually a proclamation encouraging the observance of [these months.] this month.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
