Senate Amendment No. 508 to Senate Bill No. 297 Page 4
1 Sec. 3. 1. The month of October of each year is designated as
2 “Menopause Awareness Month” in this State.
3 2. The Governor shall issue annually a proclamation encouraging the
4 observance of Menopause Awareness Month. The proclamation must, without
5 limitation, call upon news media, health care providers, educators, nonprofit
6 groups and foundations, appropriate governmental officers and other public and
7 private entities to:
8 (a) Bring to the attention of the residents of this State factual information
9 and educational programs regarding menopause; and
10 (b) Promote access to quality health care during menopause to support the
11 optimal health and well-being of Nevadans.
12 Sec. 4. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.

